Policy.acknowledgement_statement: INSTRUCTIONS: This study has not provided a suggested acknowledgement statement. However, Approved Users are expected to acknowledge the Submitting Investigator(s) who submitted data from the original study to an NIH-designated data repository, the primary funding organization that supported the Submitting Investigator(s), and the NIH-designated data repository (e.g., dbGaP). The acknowledgment statement should include the dbGaP accession number to the specific version of the dataset(s) analyzed.
Policy.ic_specific_access_term: In addition to acknowledging the Contributing Investigator (Daphne W. Bell, Ph.D., National Human Genome Research Institute (NHGRI), National Institutes of Health (NIH), all Approved Users also agree to acknowledge in any publication of data based on and/or generated from this NIH genomic dataset that the original human samples from which the data was generated originated from the Cooperative Human Tissue Network(CNTN).

GSR_Access.gsr_mode_label: Unrestricted access (institution did not respond within six months)

ConsentGroup.title: Disease-Specific (Endometrial Cancer, COL, NPU, GSO)
ConsentGroup.name: DS-ECA-COL-NPU-GSO
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction: Use of the data must be related to Endometrial Cancer. Requestor must provide a letter of collaboration with the primary study investigator(s). Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations. Use of the data is limited to genetic studies only.
